  <front>
    <title>EAP-based Authentication Service for CoAP</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-marin-ace-wg-coap-eap-02"/>
    <author initials="R. S." surname="Sanchez" fullname="Raul Sanchez Sanchez"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Marin-Lopez" fullname="Rafael Marin-Lopez"/>
    <author initials="D." surname="Garcia-Carrillo" fullname="Dan Garcia-Carrillo"/>
    <date day="19" month="October" year="2015"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   This document describes an authentication service that uses EAP
   transported by means of CoAP messages with two purposes:

   o  Authenticate two CoAP endpoints.

   o  Bootstrap key material to protect CoAP messages exchanged between
      them.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
